article.headline: Wright St. 78, Cleveland St. 67
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- DaShaun Wood scored 26 points, including 8-of-8 free throws, to lead Wright State to a 78-67 win over Cleveland State on Thursday night. Eight of Wood's points came during a 16-2 Raiders run that pulled Wright State ahead 26-12 about 13 minutes into the game. Todd Brown and Jordan Pleiman added 14 points apiece for Wright State (12-7, 5-1 Horizon League) and Drew Burleson added 11. J'Nathan Bullock led the Vikings (7-13, 1-6) with 21 points, and Bahaadar Russell and Joe Davis scored 17 each. Patrick Tatham had a game-high 12 rebounds. Cleveland State, behind 37-27 at the half, tied it at 50 with about 10 minutes left to play, but Wright State scored seven unanswered points over the next two minutes. The Raiders led by at least five points for the rest of the game.
